1
00:00:04.110 --> 00:00:08.377
Hello and welcome to BB Linköping's big lecture "To give birth".


2
00:00:09.722 --> 00:00:15.008
You are all here to listen, because you have one thing in common:


3
00:00:15.822 --> 00:00:19.753
that you are expecting a child. First, second, third or even fourth child.


4
00:00:19.931 --> 00:00:21.038
What do we know?


5
00:00:21.685 --> 00:00:26.536
This lecture replaces the actual lecture


6
00:00:26.779 --> 00:00:29.450
we normally have a few times each semester


7
00:00:29.704 --> 00:00:31.531
at the US in Linköping.


8
00:00:32.139 --> 00:00:37.032
Since we have a pandemic, we have to use this remedy.


9
00:00:38.343 --> 00:00:43.937
We will not go into anything about the corona restrictions


10
00:00:44.332 --> 00:00:48.080
because they change often, sometimes from day to day.


11
00:00:48.735 --> 00:00:53.581
We may refer to the region's guidelines and the Public Health Agency.


12
00:00:54.901 --> 00:00:59.552
My name is Lina Broberg and I work as a midwife at the birth in Linköping.


13
00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:05.587
My name is Caroline Lorentzon. I also work on childbirth and BB.


14
00:01:10.509 --> 00:01:12.486
Today's agenda you see here:


15
00:01:13.179 --> 00:01:16.916
We thought we would tell you how we work at the birth-


16
00:01:17.328 --> 00:01:20.896
Who works with us and how we work together.


17
00:01:21.407 --> 00:01:25.288
We will also talk about how you can prepare for your birth.


18
00:01:25.775 --> 00:01:29.779
And what happens when you come to us at the birth.


19
00:01:30.967 --> 00:01:34.482
We go through the different stages of childbirth.


20
00:01:35.489 --> 00:01:38.905
The focus will be on the normal birth process.


21
00:01:39.386 --> 00:01:44.560
But we will also talk a little about when the process deviates from the normal.


22
00:01:45.277 --> 00:01:50.114
In the end, we talk about pain and pain relief,


23
00:01:50.426 --> 00:01:53.984
both non-medical and medical.


24
00:01:59.296 --> 00:02:00.944
This is what our entrance looks like.


25
00:02:02.148 --> 00:02:07.715
We are located next to the emergency room and recommend that you take the "outside road".


26
00:02:08.670 --> 00:02:11.425
That you do not try to find your way in the


27
00:02:11.747 --> 00:02:15.035
culvert, but follow the signs to the delivery and the emergency room.


28
00:02:15.692 --> 00:02:17.472
Then you will come to this door.


29
00:02:18.325 --> 00:02:22.083
It is often open, so when you arrive you can try to slam the door a little.


30
00:02:22.794 --> 00:02:24.696
If it's open, just step in


31
00:02:25.251 --> 00:02:28.033
and take the elevator up to floor 12. There we are.


32
00:02:28.980 --> 00:02:31.817
On evenings, nights and weekends the door is locked.


33
00:02:32.222 --> 00:02:35.074
Then there's an intercom you can call on


34
00:02:36.893 --> 00:02:40.004
... ... we let you in and you go up to floor 12.


35
00:02:43.556 --> 00:02:48.520
The blue arrow you see there should illustrate one of our parking lots


36
00:02:48.843 --> 00:02:52.744
... ... just outside the entrance. You can stand there for 30 minutes.


37
00:02:53.171 --> 00:02:54.751
Then you need to move the car.


38
00:02:55.076 --> 00:02:59.320
Either to the parking garage at the north entrance


39
00:02:59.625 --> 00:03:02.102
or to the large parking lot at the south entrance.


40
00:03:02.578 --> 00:03:06.929
The red arrow points to the entrance that was in the picture before.


41
00:03:10.455 --> 00:03:14.769
This is what it looks like when you get to floor 12 and into the department.


42
00:03:15.153 --> 00:03:19.311
Unfortunately, there are not always two happy midwives waiting in the


43
00:03:19.624 --> 00:03:20.624
hall when you arrive.


44
00:03:21.208 --> 00:03:28.295
But by the frosted glass on the window, the coordinator has her little haunt,


45
00:03:28.897 --> 00:03:30.712
and she usually sits in the booth.


46
00:03:31.298 --> 00:03:33.792
If nothing else, our expedition is right inside


47
00:03:34.088 --> 00:03:38.406
... ... and we always move around the entrance so we know when you're coming.


48
00:03:42.568 --> 00:03:47.800
When you come to us at the birth, it is you who are in focus.


49
00:03:49.200 --> 00:03:56.921
All our work; 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, is all about you.


50
00:03:57.421 --> 00:04:01.436
About you as expectant parents and about the child.


51
00:04:01.736 --> 00:04:03.554
It is you who are in focus.


52
00:04:04.061 --> 00:04:09.446
Around you there is a whole team of professional people


53
00:04:10.020 --> 00:04:15.463
... ... where there are mainly midwives you will meet ... ... assistant


54
00:04:16.994 --> 00:04:22.313
nurses. We have many very good, experienced assistant nurses


55
00:04:22.665 --> 00:04:28.935
with us, who give you good advice and good support.


56
00:04:30.606 --> 00:04:34.971
We have a very professional group of doctors with us as well.


57
00:04:36.640 --> 00:04:39.983
It is not always possible to see a doctor when giving birth.


58
00:04:40.355 --> 00:04:46.371
Sometimes you meet one or two midwives, no doctor.


59
00:04:46.953 --> 00:04:48.033
This is perfectly normal.


60
00:04:48.296 --> 00:04:51.321
Sometimes a doctor needs to be


61
00:04:53.051 --> 00:04:56.754
called in to discuss how your birth is progressing.


62
00:04:58.034 --> 00:05:01.296
It does not have to be something dangerous or "danger and journey" - -


63
00:05:01.531 --> 00:05:04.155
but that is how we work in the team at BB Linköping.


64
00:05:05.824 --> 00:05:10.690
Because we are a university hospital, we often have students with us.


65
00:05:11.274 --> 00:05:17.787
Then it is primarily midwifery students but also future doctors.


66
00:05:18.615 --> 00:05:23.352
These midwifery students are all nurses at heart


67
00:05:23.687 --> 00:05:28.166
and have usually worked in healthcare for at least a year.


68
00:05:28.472 --> 00:05:29.912
Often longer than that.


69
00:05:32.618 --> 00:05:37.376
We can really strike a blow to have midwifery students with us.


70
00:05:37.627 --> 00:05:40.107
There's another aspect to it all,


71
00:05:40.441 --> 00:05:44.256
and another person who's there just for you, during the birth.


72
00:05:45.124 --> 00:05:50.628
It is still always a responsible midwife who makes decisions, together with you.


73
00:05:50.954 --> 00:05:57.410
The medical decisions are made by doctors and midwives. Not by students.


74
00:05:58.521 --> 00:06:05.185
There are many around you even if they are not visible in the hall, but in the background.


75
00:06:06.178 --> 00:06:11.354
The medical candidates with us are in their last semester ... ...


76
00:06:11.688 --> 00:06:14.586
before they go out into the real professional life.


77
00:06:14.823 --> 00:06:19.991
So it is also experienced, future colleagues you meet.


78
00:06:20.288 --> 00:06:23.112
But of course it is always voluntary.


79
00:06:23.437 --> 00:06:27.424
You can choose whether you want to bring a student with you or not.


80
00:06:27.737 --> 00:06:30.096
But we can recommend it.


81
00:06:30.386 --> 00:06:35.072
It is usually very appreciated to have a person as support and help


82
00:06:35.759 --> 00:06:37.126
during their birth.


83
00:06:39.447 --> 00:06:42.936
Here you see a picture of how we work in our team,


84
00:06:43.351 --> 00:06:45.313
outside the delivery room.


85
00:06:46.006 --> 00:06:49.794
In the picture we have a doctor and four midwives.


86
00:06:50.263 --> 00:06:52.778
Sometimes it can be that the birth stops.


87
00:06:53.705 --> 00:06:57.681
Maybe the child has adjusted a little differently in the pelvis.


88
00:06:58.486 --> 00:07:01.623
That may be one reason we need to discuss


89
00:07:01.920 --> 00:07:04.744
how we can move forward, how this child is doing.


90
00:07:05.023 --> 00:07:09.888
That we need to share different advice, tips and our skills.


91
00:07:10.562 --> 00:07:12.864
This is not a secret to you,


92
00:07:13.114 --> 00:07:17.447
but sometimes it's a little easier for us to walk out of the room and talk to each other


93
00:07:18.196 --> 00:07:21.019
... ... and then come in to you and make further suggestions


94
00:07:21.274 --> 00:07:23.967
... ... how can we continue to work during the birth?


95
00:07:24.512 --> 00:07:29.199
But as I said: We work together in the department all the time.


96
00:07:29.551 --> 00:07:33.087
Even if it's a midwife and an assistant nurse


97
00:07:33.239 --> 00:07:35.158
who is responsible for your birth


98
00:07:35.353 --> 00:07:38.718
, we are all involved in all births


99
00:07:39.011 --> 00:07:41.025
and in several decisions as well.


100
00:07:42.486 --> 00:07:45.921
We will go on and talk about how we work on childbirth.


101
00:07:46.554 --> 00:07:49.466
Each work shift has a coordinator.


102
00:07:50.200 --> 00:07:57.210
The coordinator is an experienced midwife who has a managerial role.


103
00:07:58.240 --> 00:08:02.752
One of her main tasks is to answer the phone when you call.


104
00:08:03.525 --> 00:08:07.304
Telephone counseling is a big part of her job.


105
00:08:07.929 --> 00:08:10.855
She has a coordinating function


106
00:08:11.120 --> 00:08:14.914
... ... and distributes the women who will give birth ...


107
00:08:15.092 --> 00:08:18.653
... to the midwives who work on the shift, and the assistant nurses.


108
00:08:20.680 --> 00:08:25.095
Then we collaborate with a number of other clinics.


109
00:08:25.670 --> 00:08:31.273
First of all, the neonatal ward right next to the maternity ward.


110
00:08:31.618 --> 00:08:36.313
So we have both physically close to there but also a close collaboration with NEO.


111
00:08:37.644 --> 00:08:40.996
It may be a baby that you already know before the birth


112
00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:46.257
will need to be observed or cared for at the NEO after the birth.


113
00:08:46.513 --> 00:08:50.841
But it can also be children who after the birth


114
00:08:51.046 --> 00:08:53.533
... ... show signs that they need a little extra care


115
00:08:53.795 --> 00:08:58.319
... ... or are observed, for a few hours or days on NEO.


116
00:08:58.891 --> 00:09:02.933
And the children where it is already known that they need


117
00:09:03.143 --> 00:09:07.587
care at NEO. It can be children who are born prematurely, for example ... ...


118
00:09:08.112 --> 00:09:11.935
or where you look at the supervision during the final stages of the birth


119
00:09:12.173 --> 00:09:14.215
... ... that support and help will probably be needed here.


120
00:09:15.017 --> 00:09:18.085
We call the NEO team as we call it


121
00:09:19.603 --> 00:09:22.689
in different situations during childbirth.


122
00:09:22.869 --> 00:09:24.680
For example, if there is a suction


123
00:09:24.973 --> 00:09:29.984
cup, there are always NEO staff outside the room, should they be needed.


124
00:09:30.254 --> 00:09:33.167
Usually they are not needed but can turn around and leave


125
00:09:33.399 --> 00:09:36.720
when the baby is out. But we want them to be in place.


126
00:09:38.650 --> 00:09:41.952
In addition to NEO, we collaborate a lot with anesthetists.


127
00:09:42.811 --> 00:09:46.652
On the one hand, there are those who are responsible for pain relief or anesthesia ... ...


128
00:09:46.900 --> 00:09:48.530
should it be the case that


129
00:09:48.707 --> 00:09:52.687
for some reason they need surgery during or after their birth.


130
00:09:53.389 --> 00:09:58.906
They are also the ones who put back anesthesia if you wish when you are going to give birth to your child.


131
00:10:00.447 --> 00:10:03.860
We want you to know that they always do their utmost


132
00:10:04.128 --> 00:10:07.703
to get there as quickly as possible, but sometimes they are busy


133
00:10:08.238 --> 00:10:13.520
at surgery, IVA or the emergency room.


134
00:10:13.793 --> 00:10:15.750
Then it may be a while before they arrive.


135
00:10:16.895 --> 00:10:19.252
But their goal is to get there as soon as possible.


136
00:10:20.620 --> 00:10:26.850
We also collaborate with other hospitals, mainly Vrinnevis Hospital in Norrköping.


137
00:10:28.760 --> 00:10:31.863
It may be that we are full with us or for some reason


138
00:10:32.105 --> 00:10:35.520
... ... can not receive you, when you call in for the birth.


139
00:10:36.025 --> 00:10:38.928
Then we sometimes need to refer to another hospital.


140
00:10:39.583 --> 00:10:44.535
In the first place, it is Norrköping we are referring to because it is closest.


141
00:10:45.993 --> 00:10:50.139
Those in Norrköping have access to your medical records, just like us.


142
00:10:50.594 --> 00:10:58.008
They can read about how your pregnancy was and if you made any wishes there.


143
00:11:00.576 --> 00:11:04.943
When we refer to it, we do it for you.


144
00:11:05.640 --> 00:11:07.641
In order for you to receive the best possible care.


145
00:11:07.955 --> 00:11:10.702
That there should be a midwife, assistant nurse and doctor ... ... who


146
00:11:11.100 --> 00:11:16.003
has the opportunity to receive you and give you support when you are about to give birth to your child.


147
00:11:18.105 --> 00:11:24.045
We know that it is a concern many carry with them before the birth.


148
00:11:24.296 --> 00:11:27.135
A worry about being referred to another hospital.


149
00:11:27.455 --> 00:11:31.376
It's not often, but it does happen. And it will be good anyway.


150
00:11:33.990 --> 00:11:36.192
We also collaborate with Kvinnohälsan


151
00:11:37.160 --> 00:11:41.223
when it comes to checks and such during your pregnancy.


152
00:11:43.184 --> 00:11:45.153
Education, it says there.


153
00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:50.124
We go to continuous training, we who work as midwives,


154
00:11:50.386 --> 00:11:53.711
assistant nurses and doctors in the team that Lina talked about.


155
00:11:54.466 --> 00:11:57.718
We have exercises where we train together


156
00:11:58.030 --> 00:12:00.914
in situations that do not occur so often,


157
00:12:01.761 --> 00:12:05.975
but we need to be good at, be able to act quickly, when it happens.


158
00:12:06.639 --> 00:12:13.066
There we have continuous exercises and training situations.


159
00:12:13.657 --> 00:12:18.282
Maybe you want to give some examples of some exercises we have?


160
00:12:18.679 --> 00:12:22.563
We train partly on seat births, for example.


161
00:12:22.962 --> 00:12:24.938
It's not very common but it does happen sometimes.


162
00:12:25.195 --> 00:12:27.771
Then we get to practice on dolls, the pelvis and the


163
00:12:28.510 --> 00:12:32.399
different grips you use during a seat birth.


164
00:12:33.415 --> 00:12:36.083
Same thing with suction cup. We train that too.


165
00:12:36.300 --> 00:12:41.879
And children's exercises, where we train to take care of children who are


166
00:12:42.395 --> 00:12:44.930
not feeling so well at birth. Who need some extra breathing


167
00:12:45.899 --> 00:12:48.245
support, for example, when they come out.


168
00:12:49.402 --> 00:12:52.880
As Lina said before, we are a university hospital,


169
00:12:53.492 --> 00:12:58.298
which means that, more or less, research is always conducted there.


170
00:12:58.735 --> 00:13:04.344
It may be that, during your stay, you are asked if you want to participate in a study.


171
00:13:04.649 --> 00:13:06.980
You may have already received that question from Women's Health


172
00:13:07.243 --> 00:13:09.797
and are included in a study already when you come to us.


173
00:13:10.454 --> 00:13:11.729
This is of course voluntary.


174
00:13:11.986 --> 00:13:16.759
Even if you have agreed to a study, you can choose to cancel at any time.


175
00:13:22.946 --> 00:13:29.931
When you call the delivery, it is always the coordinator who answers.


176
00:13:30.659 --> 00:13:33.675
It's an experienced midwife who has worked for many years in


177
00:13:33.909 --> 00:13:35.339
maternity care.


178
00:13:36.941 --> 00:13:43.082
We work three shifts at the birth. Morning, afternoon, evening or night.


179
00:13:44.106 --> 00:13:47.926
Then you change coordinator on the three shifts.


180
00:13:49.048 --> 00:13:54.059
Many times when you call us you get to talk to the same person.


181
00:13:54.379 --> 00:13:58.513
We experience that you often think it is a security.


182
00:13:58.947 --> 00:14:04.664
If you first call maybe eight in the morning and then Sofia answers the phone.


183
00:14:05.468 --> 00:14:09.038
When you call next time at ten o'clock, it is Sofia who also answers.


184
00:14:09.407 --> 00:14:11.765
Then you do not have to tell your whole story again


185
00:14:12.020 --> 00:14:15.823
... ... without her knowing that you are there and what you've talked about before.


186
00:14:16.128 --> 00:14:21.360
Of course, you always keep a record of what the discussion has been about.


187
00:14:21.775 --> 00:14:24.991
It can feel a little nice for you to hear the same voice.


188
00:14:25.319 --> 00:14:28.577
It is our experience and the feedback we usually get.


189
00:14:29.929 --> 00:14:32.109
When to call for childbirth?


190
00:14:32.422 --> 00:14:37.658
You should call when you suspect that the birth has started.


191
00:14:38.059 --> 00:14:41.673
For example, through aches, if the water has gone or


192
00:14:41.950 --> 00:14:47.955
if you get bleeding. Or if you feel uncertain about these aspects.


193
00:14:48.356 --> 00:14:52.033
Sometimes, when you are expecting your first child, it is not always so easy to know,


194
00:14:52.407 --> 00:14:54.207
what is it like when the water goes?


195
00:14:54.757 --> 00:14:56.256
This has not been the case before.


196
00:14:56.553 --> 00:14:58.796
It is not really known how much water will come.


197
00:14:59.108 --> 00:15:01.433
Or how much is a bleed?


198
00:15:01.756 --> 00:15:07.639
Is it a little pink on the toilet paper or like a menstrual bleeding?


199
00:15:08.100 --> 00:15:10.577
Then you call and play ball with us.


200
00:15:12.163 --> 00:15:15.969
If you have questions you do not judge as urgent


201
00:15:16.318 --> 00:15:21.775
... ... but think it could wait a bit ...


202
00:15:22.568 --> 00:15:25.815
We understand that it is difficult for you who are sitting there at home


203
00:15:26.237 --> 00:15:30.497
... ... but if you think that it is not something that needs to be checked right here and now


204
00:15:30.843 --> 00:15:34.057
, we are happy to refer you to Kvinnohälsan.


205
00:15:34.693 --> 00:15:37.021
We know it can be a little difficult to get hold of them.


206
00:15:37.284 --> 00:15:41.975
We also recommend going to "my care contacts" via 1177.


207
00:15:42.241 --> 00:15:46.216
There you can write a message. Then the staff at Kvinnohälsan will


208
00:15:46.482 --> 00:15:48.587
respond within a couple of days.


209
00:15:52.861 --> 00:15:58.883
We also always want you to call the delivery before you arrive.


210
00:15:59.256 --> 00:16:03.128
Even if you feel confident that now the birth has started,


211
00:16:03.422 --> 00:16:07.421
now I have painful pains, with fairly frequent intervals,


212
00:16:07.690 --> 00:16:11.487
I feel confident in this. Maybe you are a surrogate mother, have children before.


213
00:16:11.910 --> 00:16:14.847
We still want you to call this phone number


214
00:16:16.486 --> 00:16:19.835
so we can receive you in the best possible way when you arrive.


215
00:16:20.506 --> 00:16:25.830
We want you to receive good care and a nice welcome.


216
00:16:26.172 --> 00:16:29.413
We increase the conditions for that if we know that you are on your way.


217
00:16:31.233 --> 00:16:35.472
The phone number you see here: Feel free to put it in your phones


218
00:16:35.834 --> 00:16:37.373
so you have it available.


219
00:16:38.347 --> 00:16:40.579
Preparation for childbirth.


220
00:16:40.885 --> 00:16:43.299
How can you prepare for the birth of a child,


221
00:16:43.583 --> 00:16:45.513
regardless of which child in the order it is?


222
00:16:46.091 --> 00:16:52.025
We've lined up a few different circles around how to do ... ...


223
00:16:52.287 --> 00:16:55.239
to feel mentally and perhaps physically ready


224
00:16:55.516 --> 00:16:57.264
for the upcoming birth.


225
00:16:57.764 --> 00:17:02.705
What we think is most important is what is most marked: The


226
00:17:02.982 --> 00:17:06.120
parental support we offer you here and now.


227
00:17:06.643 --> 00:17:09.018
Just by listening to Caroline and me


228
00:17:09.252 --> 00:17:17.142
today ... ... have you come a long way on the "birth preparation path".


229
00:17:18.161 --> 00:17:21.566
However, you should not feel that you have to know this.


230
00:17:21.807 --> 00:17:25.391
That it's a test, an exam, you have to go through.


231
00:17:25.678 --> 00:17:28.805
This is some advice and support.


232
00:17:29.068 --> 00:17:34.700
That there is a bit in the back of my mind about how a birth can go.


233
00:17:36.103 --> 00:17:38.638
A little what can be good to know.


234
00:17:38.809 --> 00:17:43.571
But you should not split up that this is exactly how it will be.


235
00:17:43.841 --> 00:17:46.157
That this is how I should


236
00:17:46.434 --> 00:17:50.520
feel - without having a thought about "how would I like it to be?" -


237
00:17:50.833 --> 00:17:52.755
-but still have an open mind ... ...


